---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home">
  <article class="hero">
    <h1>The World Transformed</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Economics, Policy, and Coordination Mechanisms</p>

    <section class="intro">
      <p>
        Matt Kilcoyne. Policy analyst at the Center for Data Innovation and ITIF.
        Based in London. Navigator of possibility space.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="focus-areas">
      <h2>Focus Areas</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Economics</h3>
          <p>Institutional economics, Austrian school, market-oriented policy analysis</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Technology Policy</h3>
          <p>AI governance, digital sovereignty, EU regulation (DMA, DSA, AI Act)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Philosophy</h3>
          <p>Political philosophy, ethics of technology, coordination problems</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Coordination Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Mechanism design, collective action, rent-seeking analysis</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="current-work">
      <h2>Current Research</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The Babel Navigation Theorem: Formalizing LLMs as possibility space search tools</li>
        <li>Digital sovereignty critique: Analyzing European tech protectionism</li>
        <li>Infrastructure economics: How policy creates or eliminates rent-seeking</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="principles">
      <h2>Guiding Principles</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Navigation beats prediction</li>
        <li>Follow the money</li>
        <li>People should be able to raise kids in peace</li>
        <li>All in this together, to the stars and new dimensions</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="tools">
      <h2>Tools</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/brunel" class="button">The Brunel Engine</a> -
        Turn frustrations into actionable insight through structured interviews.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #58a6ff;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #8b949e;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  section {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #c9d1d9;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #58a6ff;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .card {
    border: 1px solid #30363d;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #161b22;
  }

  ul, ol {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  li {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #238636;
    color: white;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .button:hover {
    background: #2ea043;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
